The incident happened after a chase on the N3 North, when police followed a truck to Marlboro after a hijacking. JOHANNESBURG - Police have arrested two suspects in connection with a truck hijacking in which two people were shot, including a Metro police officer.The incident happened after a chase on the N3 North, near the Buccleuch interchange.Police had followed the truck to Marlboro and confronted the suspects as they were offloading cellphones.The police's Mavela Masondo said: When the police confronted the suspects, there was a shoot-out between the police and the suspects. That s when a Metro police officer was shot in the upper body and he was taken to hospital. (Edited by Refilwe Thobega)